1. Problem Statement

School IT had no structured Active Directory. User accounts were created manually and inconsistently.

2. Environment
Windows Server 2012 R2
Active Directory Domain Services
1 Domain Controller
~60users (teachers & admin)

3. Implementation Process
Install AD DS role on Windows Server
Promote server to Domain Controller
Create OU structure:
Teachers
Admin
Create bulk users using PowerShell:
New-ADUser
Apply Group Policies:
Password policy
Account lockout rules
Join PCs to domain

4. Pros
Centralized user management
Faster onboarding
Standardised security policies

5. Cons
Single domain controller risk (no redundancy)
Manual scripting still required for bulk users
Limited automation

6. Cost Considerations
Windows Server license required
Hardware server cost
Low cost overall (small environment)

7. Security Considerations
Weak passwords initially a risk
No MFA in basic setup
Limited auditing
